nt mandates single-repo vs multi-repo — the alignment is to epic direction, not to a specific cited requirement.", "Clarified criticality rationale: rating reflects post-ticket dependency graph (per-plugin policy governs cortex-interactive + ui-extras + pr-review, and cortex-overnight-integration per ticket 121), not the pre-ticket single-plugin build recipe."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Mechanism for drift-enforcement policy (config file, hardcoded list, convention) and whether to pre-generalize for ticket 121 are implementation-level research/spec questions — the scope is bounded by specified behavior, mechanism is downstream."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "The ticket explicitly documents supersession of DR-9 for the ui-extras+pr-review subset; the user owns this decision and has written it into the ticket body. Clarify does not re-litigate user-made decisions. DR-9's 'truly orthogonal' argument is addressed by leaving android-dev-extras in the external repo; the 'opt-in per project' argument is preserved via per-plugin /plugin install (classification, not repo separation)."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Complexity tier stands as 'complex'. The git-subtree-add vs raw-copy choice is a discrete design decision, not a complexity amplifier — both are standard operations. The plugin trees being copied are small (two plugin directories) and the classification-introduction is the dominant complexity driver."}], "status": "ok"}
